      Methods in org.neo4j.graphdb.schema that return ConstraintCreator 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      ConstraintCreator ConstraintCreator.assertPropertyExists​(String propertyKey)
      Imposes an existence constraint for the given property.
      ConstraintCreator ConstraintCreator.assertPropertyIsNodeKey​(String propertyKey)
      Imposes both a uniqueness constraint, and a property existence constraint, for the given property.
      ConstraintCreator ConstraintCreator.assertPropertyIsUnique​(String propertyKey)
      Imposes a uniqueness constraint for the given property.
      ConstraintCreator Schema.constraintFor​(Label label)
      Returns a ConstraintCreator where details about the constraint can be specified.
      ConstraintCreator Schema.constraintFor​(RelationshipType type)
      Returns a ConstraintCreator where details about the constraint can be specified.
      ConstraintCreator ConstraintCreator.withIndexConfiguration​(Map<IndexSetting,​Object> indexConfiguration)
      Set index-specific index configurations.
      ConstraintCreator ConstraintCreator.withIndexType​(IndexType indexType)
      Assign an index type to the constraint.
      ConstraintCreator ConstraintCreator.withName​(String name)
      Assign a name to the constraint, which will then be returned from ConstraintDefinition.getName(), and can be used for finding the constraint with Schema.getConstraintByName(String), or the associated index with Schema.getIndexByName(String) for index backed constraints.
